title.11: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #3

description.0: The Mandarin is back and he's planning something big! The Avengers scramble across the globe to stop him, but can their efforts really triumph over the Mandarin's villainy? Plus, and unexpected appearance of Ultimo!
description.1: Chaos ensues as the Avengers attack Colonel Ying's base. The Red Guardian proves to be a formidable match for Captain America, but there's something oddly familiar about this Super Soldier.
description.2: Kidnapped by the Cobra and Mr. Hyde, Daredevil, still without his powers, finds himself entirely off-kilter! How will DD escape the stickiest situation of his career? And will his super powers ever be restored?
description.4: The most deadly, demoniacal foe of all-The Merciless Mordo is back!
description.5: The TITANIUM MAN lives again! Can Iron Man defeat a foe whose armor is superior to his own?
description.6: The High Evolutionary deploys the Hulk as a weapon of mass destruction to a mysterious planet!
description.7: Odin faces his own challenger, while Thor, Sif and Balder have a scrape with Magnir and Brona. And, Volstagg takes center stage in his own tale of mystery!
description.9: The First Cameo Appearance of Adam Warlock, originally known as Him!  What is the Beehive? From whence did it emerge? A mysterious enclave of scientists kidnaps Alicia Masters.
description.12: The first appearance of Forbush Man!  Four spoofy stories in one bust-out-loud-laughing issue! Here, meet the mighty Silver Burper! Then, you’ve read the fateful meeting between original Young Allies Human Torch and the Sub-Mariner, but have you met…The Human Scorch and Sunk-Mariner?!
description.13: When the Kingpin orders that J. Jonah Jameson be silenced for his negative press on Fisk's illegal activites, Spidey swings in to save the EIC. But can the Wallcrawler take the big guy in a one-on-one brawl?
description.14: Hawkeye and Hercules get information about Black Widow's whereabouts and set out to rescue her, but to their surprise they are ambushed by the Red Guardian, Colonel Ying's secret weapon. Plus, Quicksilver discovers a shocking new ability!
description.16: Robbed of his super senses by Mr. Hyde, Matt Murdock realizes what it's like to be truly blind! How will Daredevil navigate life as a super hero without his super powers? And will Matt be able to trust those closest to him?
description.18: Dr. Strange returns to his Greenwich Village hideaway-only to that the entire building has mysteriously vanished!
description.19: When Iron Man is called to the battlefield for weapon testing, little does he know the true mission that awaits him - one that he might not survive! Plus: Cap races against time to stop a sinister plot: the assassination of Nick Fury!
description.20: We won't tell you how this issue starts, but we'll tell you how it ends...with the Hulk floating in space towards a destination unknown!
description.21: Thor is joined by Asgardian comrades Balder and Sif to subdue the Enchanters Three...and the Living Talisman to boot!
description.23: The Kree retaliate! After the FF destroys their Sentry, the Kree's Supreme Intelligence unleashes its mightiest warlord. Check out the first appearance of Ronan the Accuser!
description.25: One of the most iconic Spider-Man stories - SPIDER-MAN NO MORE!  Peter becomes frustrated with his life and decides to throw away his Spider-Man outfit and quit being Spider-Man.  What will it take to remind Peter that with great power comes great responsibility?
description.26: Qucksilver teams up with Hawkeye, the Scarlet Witch, and Hercules to track down Diablo. But can they find him in time to stop him from reactivating Dragon Man and unleashing his immense power?
description.27: Daredevil ticks off Thor, God of Thunder! What has Daredevil done to run afoul of the Mighty Thunderer? And how are the Cobra and Mr. Hyde involved?  Daredevil learns not to mess with Asgardian royalty by receiving a smack down he won't soon forget!
description.29: Dr. Strange must face "The Sands of Death!"
description.30: Introducing the CRUSHER! He's on an unstoppable rampage, and his target: Iron Man!
description.31: The Hulk wishes upon the Silver Surfer to take him far away from Earth, where all of his pain and hardship was born. Will the Cosmic Wanderer answers his pleas?
description.32: Loki orchestrates a new plan to destroy Thor by instigating an attack by the deadly Super-Skrull on the God of Thunder!
description.34: An exotic vacation turned extraterrestrial warfront! Sounds like a typical getaway for the FF- will the team be able to defeat the Kree tech of Sentry #459?
description.37: Daredevil unmasked? Matt nearly reveals his secret identity to Karen Page, but his plans are thrown off by Masked Marauder's goons! With Karen kidnapped, and Foggy in critical condition, will Daredevil be able to fight off Marauder's men, and save the girl he loves?
description.39: Now that Umar is gone, Zom becomes the deadliest menace of all and tries to kill Dr. Strange!
description.40: The battle between Iron Man and the Melter rages on, until the Golden Avenger pulls out his trump card! Plus, the Red Skull presents Cap with an impossible ultimatum: his loyalty to his country? Or its survival?
description.41: Will Chuda's plan for world domination come to fruition? Not if Slugger Sykes has his say! Meanwhile, Thor takes on the mighty Replicus.
description.42: Mister Fantastic has been pulled from the Negative Zone...but so has living bomb Blastaar! Sandman and Blastaar rampage against the FF. Good thing Inhuman friends Crystal and Triton are on hand for battle!
description.44: Hearing about the Vulture's defeat of Spider-Man, Kraven becomes furious that he was denied his right to defeat the wall crawler and vows to hunt down his new enemy.
description.45: Black Widow falls victim to Colonel Ying and Dr. Yen's latest invention, the Psychotron. Meanwhile, Goliath conducts tests on Dragon Man, while Diablo plots to use him for his own sinister plans.
description.48: Invaders from outer-space! While giving a college lecture on the legal implications of an alien invasion, Matt Murdock's super sense is alerted to extraterrestrial activity!  Enter the Queega, a strange alien race intent on robbing the world of sight! Will Daredevil's blindness be an asset in this race against the clock?
description.50: In order to vanquish the unspeakable Umar, Dr. Strange has liberated Zom from an imprisonment of ages!
description.51: Old enemies resurface! First, Iron Man must contend with a new and improved Melter! Then: Captain America confronts his deadliest foe: the Red Skull!
description.52: One giant green beast versus another...Hulk takes on the Abomination!
description.53: Will Thor be triumphant over the Growing Man? And which familiar villain spawned this gargantuan foe?
description.55: Reed Richards stands alone in the Negative Zone! But his isolation is soon broken by the mighty Blastaar! In the Baxter Building, the Inhumans scramble with the FF to recover their missing leader.
description.56: Spider-Man searches the city for a trace of Kraven the Hunter.
description.58: Kraven the Hunter hunts...Norman Osborn?  Can Spidey stop one enemy from destroying another?
description.61: Daredevil gets involved in one of Spider-Man's tussles, leading to rocky terms with the wall-crawler. Meanwhile Masked Marauder and Stilt-Man combine forces to take down the Man Without Fear once and for all! But with both villains hunting for "Mike Murdock", will their trail run cold before they begin?
description.63: In this issue, Dr. Strange must face "The Fearful Finish." But, even as the deadly blast hurtles towards its helpless victim, Dr. Strange must desperately move with the speed of thought...
description.64: Iron Man's showdown with the Mole Man reaches its explosive climax! And Captain America receives a distress call from...Bucky Barnes!?
description.65: The First Appearance of the Abomination!  A gamma-powered brute who can go punch for punch with the Hulk!  Plus, Bruce Banner comes to the point where he must dose himself with deadly gamma rays to fight on…
description.66: The Asgardian Troll War heats up, as Lady Sif leads Thor to Trollheim to do battle with Ulik and his ilk. Will Orikal be freed at least?
description.68: Sandman's stalking the FF! And when Mister Fantastic falls into the Negative Zone, his teammates fear for the worst!
description.72: Peter moves in with Harry and is confronted by The Shocker for the first time!
description.73: Daredevil takes Stilt Man to court! After his attempt to rescue Leap Frog from the stand goes awry, Stilt-Man faces the wrath of Daredevil. The American judicial systems as you've never seen it before! Plus, the civilian identity of Masked Marauder revealed!
description.75: The unspeakable Umar hurls a spell of death across the infinite void to where Clea is imprisoned! Nick Fury comes in to help Dr. Strange!
description.76: A test run of a Stark Industries drill goes south when the Mole Man intervenes!
description.77: One who is Unworthy steals the hammer of Thor! But will they be able to wield Mjolnir? Plus, behold the mystic might of the Orb of Orikal!
description.79: Doomsday for the Silver Surfer! Robbed of power and imprisoned in Latveria, the Surfer continues to be tortured by Doom's guards.  Will Galactus' herald plot his escape? The Inhumans start to construct their new home following the fall of Attilan!
description.81: The Lizard heads to Dr. Connor's lab to find a formula to transform reptiles into his personal army...
description.82: Introducing Daredevil's third identity! After Foggy and Karen suspect Matt is Daredevil, Murdock creates a fictional twin brother, Mike Murdock. But a greater threat emerges when DD is attacked by a costumed villain wearing spring loaded shoes...the first appearance of Leap Frog!
description.84: This issue has Dr. Strange lured into the deadliest of traps! He needs to free the innocent Clea from captivity, but he is forced to confront the murderous army of mindless ones!
description.85: Iron Man Mark IV is GO! With his new armor, can Tony Stark defeat the Mandarin once and for all? Plus: Captain America must save the world from the mysterious weapon known as the Z-Ray!
description.86: Just when you thought you threw 'em away, the Boomerang comes right back...
description.87: Ulik's first appearance! When Lady Sif is captured by Geirrodur, King of the Trolls, Thor is lured into battle. But Thor isn't expecting as worthy a combatant as Ulik, the Rock Trolls' most powerful warrior!
description.89: The Inhumans, free at last! Black Bolt shatters the barrier that has trapped the Inhumans in the Hidden Land. In New York, the Fantastic Four must play military strategist and world savior in the global battle against Doom!
description.90: Before Johnny Blaze, before the Spirit of Vengeance, there was Carter Slade -- the first GHOST RIDER, and the world's most mysterious Western hero!
description.94: Dr. Connors reacts from The Rhino antidote he was previously working on and turns into The Lizard. Realizing this, he runs away but is spotted by his son Billy. The Lizard plots his human conquest and plans to defeat Spider-Man.
description.95: Ka-Zar goes savage! While in Europe at a Maggia base, Daredevil catches wind of Ka-Zar's latest antics. Who is the "midnight stalker" menacing London? And how is he connected to Ka-Zar? Daredevil and Ka-Zar team up to uncover this murder mystery!
description.97: Into the Dimension of Death! Dr. Strange finds himself hurtling through the endless wastes of nowhere, on a fateful journey to the dark dimension beyond the furthest reach of mortal comprehension!
description.98: A tale of dual duels! Tony Stark must save Happy Hogan from the Mandarin - by building a new suit of armor! And Cap locks horns with one of his most persistent foes - Batroc the Leaper!
description.99: The Hulk is so powerful, a villain must be created to destroy him. Thus brings the battle of Hulk vs. Hulk-Killer!

8.text: As the X-Men try to raise money for a trip to Europe to rescue Xavier, a misguided youth dons the villainous guise of Mekano!

10.text: Who says a comic book has to be good?? Featuring the stories "Peter Pooper Vs. Gnatman and Rotten", "Magnut, Robot Biter!" and "The Blunder Agents”! This comic is unlike any that you have EVER read before!

12.text: Four spoofy stories in one bust-out-loud-laughing issue! Here, meet the mighty Silver Burper! Then, you’ve read the fateful meeting between original Young Allies Human Torch and the Sub-Mariner, but have you met…The Human Scorch and Sunk-Mariner?!

22.text: The X-Men face there strangest foe yet: The Spectacular Spider-Man!

25.text: John Romita created one of the most iconic and gripping Spider-Man covers...in 1967! Doing exactly what a great cover should do, the image combined with the "Spider-Man No More!" text pulls the reader in, demanding that they find out what's going on in the comic.

33.text: Professor X has been kidnapped by the enigmatic Factor Three! The X-Men must not only rescue their mentor, but their friend Ralph Roberts as well, who has been abducted by a subterranean tyrant.

36.text: The X-Men attempt to find a way to defeat the Unstoppable Juggernaut with the help of Doctor Strange!

38.text: The Sahara Desert is host to another brutal battle featuring America's good ol' boys…A.K.A. the Howling Commandos!

49.text: Guns a blazin', enemies a runnin'! The Commandos are back to work. But who will be "Absent Without Official Leave" in this issue?

54.text: A gang of bikers threaten to ruin Iceman's birthday! Meanwhile, Professor X attempts to rid the Juggernaut of his powers once and for all.

62.text: Back by popular demand! Dino Manelli stars in this wartime special -- and he's taking on Colonel Klaue and his Blitz Squad!

67.text: The X-Men's day off is interrupted by the emergence of the Cobalt Man!

74.text: The surprise you've all been waiting for…it's the Liberation of France!

78.text: Who is the mysterious Warlock, and is he a match for Marvel's Merry Mutants?

83.text: The Howling Commandos step into the Fortress of Fear! It'll take guts, brain and guile to get out of this one alive!

88.text: The X-Men battle with the Super-Adaptoid, a being that possesses all of the Avengers' powers! Will Mimic face this new foe, or join him?

96.text: The dashing Dino Manelli takes center stage in this front line, paratrooper's adventure!
